contentrichtext.text: '''Iraqi Council''' may refer to: * [[Iraqi Council for Non-Governmental Humanitarian Organisations]], one of the electoral coalitions that participated in the January 30, 2005 National Assembly legislative election in Iraq * [[Iraqi Council of Representatives]], a political council of Iraq * [[Iraqi Governing Council]], the provisional government of Iraq from July 13, 2003 to June 1, 2004 * [[Iraqi National Dialogue Council]], a Sunni Arab political party initially established as an umbrella organization of approximately 10 smaller Sunni parties to take part in the 2005 Iraqi Constitution drafting process * [[Iraqi Revolutionary Command Council]], the ultimate decision making body in Iraq before the 2003 Invasion of Iraq {{disambig}}
